parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause the inflator housing to rupture, resulting in metal fragments striking the front passenger or other occupants, possibly causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: as the issue is related to a safety recall and not a specific malfunction or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel speed sensor can cause the malfunction of various safety systems, including ABS, ESP, and traction control, which can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and a higher risk of accidents.
symptoms: Multiple warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
and brake force distribution warnings; cruise control
and 4WD systems become non-functional; vehicle accelerates on its own; transmission shifts erratically; vehicle surges; and inability to drive above 30mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective intake manifold can cause the vehicle to lose power, struggle to maintain speed, and potentially lead to accidents or traffic hazards.
symptoms: Hissing noise from the engine when accelerating
loss of speed when driving on the highway
inability to keep up with traffic

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning EGR valve can cause intermittent power loss, leading to unpredictable and hazardous driving conditions, particularly when accelerating or merging into traffic.
symptoms: jerking or loss of acceleration force when accelerating
check engine light may not be illuminated.
